HTTPCLIENT-2325 Avoid adding "; charset=" for multipart/form-data requests


Previusly, "charset" parameter was added to the Content-Type header, however adding "charset=..."
is not specified in RFC 7578, and it causes issues with (flawed?) HTTP servers.

The change does not modify ContentType.MULTIPART_FORM_DATA, and it might have backward compatibility
side-effects.

See
* https://github.com/apache/jmeter/issues/6250
* https://github.com/owasp-modsecurity/ModSecurity/commit/6e56950cdf258c9b39f12cf6eb014cb59797cfd3
* https://bz.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=61384
* https://github.com/akka/akka-http/issues/338

(#551)

commit.message:
HTTPCLIENT-2318 - Enhance PoolingHttpClientConnectionManager with isShutdown State Check.
This commit introduces an `isShutdown` method to the `PoolingHttpClientConnectionManager` class, providing a thread-safe way to check whether the connection manager has been closed. The addition leverages an existing `AtomicBoolean` closed flag to ensure that the shutdown state can be queried reliably in concurrent environments.
Upgraded HttpCore to version 5.3-alpha2
Removed unused private fields and local variables
Correct logger name
HTTPCLIENT-2151: Support for JSSE in-built endpoint identification
Internal connection operators to make use of the target name from the request URI authority
DefaultRoutePlanner to take request authority into account when determining a route for HTTPS requests
RouteInfo and HttpRoute to include the target name from the URI authority in case it differs from the target host (the host recognizes multiple authorities)
HTTPCLIENT-2316: BasicHttpClientConnectionManager incorrectly re-uses the released connection if it has been closed out by the protocol handler
HTTPCLIENT-2070: Auth cache to no longer rely on Java serialization for auth state caching
HTTPCLIENT-751: Support for RFC 2817 (Upgrading to TLS Within HTTP/1.1)
Classic ExecRuntime to support information responses (1xx)
Connect executors to update the execution context with the protocol and TLS details upon successful connect
Connection endpoints to provide TLS details and protocol version
Realigned the behavior of TLS upgrade in the classic and async connection operators
Deprecated ConnectionSocketFactory, LayeredConnectionSocketFactory and their plain and SSL implementations in favor of DefaultClientTlsStrategy
Standard client TLS strategy implementations to support upgrade of blocking sockets
